<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="62" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d62">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">701.6211/280½</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-26">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 26, 1914</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Lansing</hi>: I return the enclosed
                            reports of the alleged interview with Baron von Schoen.<note n="4" xml:id="d62fn1">
                                <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note>
                        </p>
                        <p>I hope that if there is any proper way of opening the matter with the
                            German Ambassador, it may be opened. I feel with you that there can be
                            no real doubt about the substantial authenticity of the interview and I
                            think it not only desirable, but imperative, that this gentleman should
                            not remain here.</p>
                        <p>Cordially and sincerely yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>